      <h4>Low input wild bird seed mixtures</h4>
      <img src="images/option_33.png">
      <p>Wild bird seed mixtures are popular agri-environment options can be
        eligible as Ecological Focus Areas under the Basic Payments Scheme.
        These typically involve cultivating and sowing patches of land with
        either annual or biennial mixtures of seed-bearing crops to provide both
        food for birds in winter and flowers for insects in summer. Their benefits
        for rare arable plants can be increased by managing them with minimal
        inputs of fertiliser and herbicides, siting them on light soils and rotating
        them to reduce the build-up of undesirable species. Further benefits
        can be added by leaving a cultivated, unsown margin around the edge for
        cornfield flowers and as feeding habitat for birds (see diagram). Below
        is a summary of some of the options under agri-environment schemes to
        provide this habitat:   </p>

